        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31746",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ooflorent",
                        "name": "ooflorent",
                        "displayName": "Florent Cailhol",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Actualy, when using an ini file, parse_ini_file() is used. This function handles PHP constants contrary to simplexml_load_file() which does not.\nIn order to add the constant support in Zend_Application when using xml files, Zend_Config_Xml must be rewrite.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ooflorent",
                        "name": "ooflorent",
                        "displayName": "Florent Cailhol",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-11T03:23:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-11T03:23:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31808",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "That patch could make it.\nLet's Rob review it ;-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-12T12:50:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-12T12:50:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31809",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Mind there is a typo in the patch , replace $this->_parseXMl() by $this->_parseXmlForPHPConstants() ; forgot to rename it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-12T12:54:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-12T12:54:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31873",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "-Will have a look soon. Ping me if I don't come back within a week!-\n\n\nUpdate: looked!\n\n\nProblem with patch is that it doesn't prevent constants in tag names and doesn't seem to handle concatenating constants within a string.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-16T03:41:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-16T03:56:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31874",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Imho that's not the way to go. I spoke with SpotSec about it already, and we think that you should include a namespace for inserting constants, so for example:\n\n{code}\n<bootstrap>\n    <path><zf:const zf:name=\"APPLICATION_PATH\"\/>\/Bootstrap.php<\/path>\n<\/bootstrap>\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-16T03:47:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-16T07:21:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31875",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "+1 for Bens suggestion.\n\nThis could also be used for further features later, such as XML includes (if it is decided to support them), and would add a consistend interface for such things.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-16T03:59:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-16T03:59:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31876",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I quite like Ben & SpotSec's proposal on the grounds that it is completely backwards compatible.\n\nAlso, we should put extends within the namespace for the future and check with Matthew about the namespace to use.\n\nFinally, I'd like to see the patch  :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-16T03:59:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-16T04:01:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31885",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Partly patch to fix the issue. Not all unit tests included yet, no support for namespace:extends, no documentation. Will be finished and comitted to trunk after Rob reviewed it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-16T07:20:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-16T07:20:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32037",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Patch looks okay to me. \n\nHave pinged Matthew to a-okay the concept and URI before we go ahead and implement.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-21T12:13:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-21T12:13:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32041",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=potatobob",
                        "name": "potatobob",
                        "displayName": "Geoffrey Tran",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "A namespace would simply be \"http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/Zend\/Config\" etc..., but it might be nice if \"zf\" was the default\n\n<bootstrap xmlns:foo=\"http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/Zend\/Config\">\n    <path><foo:const \/><\/path,>\n<\/bootstrap>",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=potatobob",
                        "name": "potatobob",
                        "displayName": "Geoffrey Tran",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-21T13:43:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-21T13:43:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32255",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=viatkine",
                        "name": "viatkine",
                        "displayName": "Lex Viatkin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "\"Now, create your configuration. For this tutorial, we will use an INI style configuration; you may, of course, use an XML or PHP configuration file as well.\"\n\nPlease, remove this part from documentation until this issue will be fixed. I spent 1 hour to find out \"why my XML config doesnt work.. they say it have!\"\n\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.application.quick-start.html",
                    "updateAuthor": {
